From ted.leslie at gmail.com  Fri Feb 13 06:35:18 2015
From: ted.leslie at gmail.com (ted leslie)
Date: Fri, 13 Feb 2015 01:35:18 -0500
Subject: [GTALUG] SSH Hangs
In-Reply-To: <CAMRGebjLdCfcjmpKCiqw2-Fb41o=kEuk5mRZEYKs+gBhF6+xyQ@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAMRGebjLdCfcjmpKCiqw2-Fb41o=kEuk5mRZEYKs+gBhF6+xyQ@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CAMua2SGbE6w9vG4wH91z0aavzbLbsrAd10F5phpYoFNakGDMRA@mail.gmail.com>

run tcpdump on your server when you do the outside connect.
you can
tcpdump -i eth0 -n |grep 209.122.208.175
do you don't get a tonne of crap. You may have to change eth0 to what is
appropriate.
also see if you have any iptables odd rules, or any odd routing.

-tl


