From cbbrowne at gmail.com  Thu Feb 19 22:35:36 2015
From: cbbrowne at gmail.com (Christopher Browne)
Date: Thu, 19 Feb 2015 17:35:36 -0500
Subject: [GTALUG] RAID and IX-2-dl
In-Reply-To: <alpine.LRH.2.02.1502191701300.27871@redclaw.mimosa.com>
References: <alpine.LRH.2.02.1502191618580.27871@redclaw.mimosa.com>
 <alpine.LRH.2.02.1502191701300.27871@redclaw.mimosa.com>
Message-ID: <CAFNqd5XAqDcSJ-jArZ_cnWEQf1BW=s=N43CVN=yyPV5=GHMrVQ@mail.gmail.com>

Sounds to me like "none" is the same as RAID 0, save for the
difference surrounding striping.

The *lack* of ability to treat this as a device per drive is
why I'd be not too keen on buying one of these devices.

I'd prefer to have what is commonly called "JBOD" support,
("Just a Bunch Of Drives")
and of the form where each drive is treated as a separate
device on the array.  To me, not having that is a deal breaker.

