From opengeometry at yahoo.ca  Fri Feb 20 05:10:45 2015
From: opengeometry at yahoo.ca (William Park)
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2015 00:10:45 -0500
Subject: [GTALUG] RAID and IX-2-dl
In-Reply-To: <alpine.LRH.2.02.1502191618580.27871@redclaw.mimosa.com>
References: <alpine.LRH.2.02.1502191618580.27871@redclaw.mimosa.com>
Message-ID: <20150220051045.GB9704@node1.localdomain>

Looks like each disk has 2 partitions, 
    /dev/sd[ab]1 --> /dev/md0 --> raid1 (1.8TB)
    /dev/sd[ab]2 --> /dev/md1 --> raid1 (1.8TB) or linear (3.6TB)
So, "none" is linear array.  Strange, because "none" is usually
individual drive, and it usually says "linear" if it is linear.
-- 
William


On Thu, Feb 19, 2015 at 04:56:12PM -0500, D. Hugh Redelmeier wrote:
