On Fri, Feb 20, 2015 at 12:10:45AM -0500, William Park wrote:
> Looks like each disk has 2 partitions, 
>     /dev/sd[ab]1 --> /dev/md0 --> raid1 (1.8TB)

Typo.......................................^^^^^\__ 20GB

>     /dev/sd[ab]2 --> /dev/md1 --> raid1 (1.8TB) or linear (3.6TB)
> So, "none" is linear array.  Strange, because "none" is usually
> individual drive, and it usually says "linear" if it is linear.

From cbbrowne at gmail.com  Fri Feb 20 21:40:45 2015
